DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     PPiixx is a `load and go' version of Pascal which combines the functions of
     the interpreter code translator ppii and the executor ppxx.  It uses ppii to
     translate the program in the file _n_a_m_e._p and, if there were no fatal er-
     rors during translation, causes the resulting interpreter code to be exe-
     cuted by ppxx with the specified arguments.	A temporary file is used for
     the object code; the file _o_b_j is neither created nor destroyed.

